## Configuration

{{ display_name }} stores configuration at:

- **Linux/macOS**: `~/.config/{{ project_name }}/config.{{ config_format }}`
- **Windows**: `%APPDATA%\{{ project_name }}\config.{{ config_format }}`

The `--config` flag overrides the default path.

### Example config file

{% if config_format == "yaml" %}
```yaml
# {{ project_name }} configuration
output_format: text
color: true
verbose: false
# Add your settings here
```
{% elif config_format == "toml" %}
```toml
# {{ project_name }} configuration
output_format = "text"
color = true
verbose = false
# Add your settings here
```
{% elif config_format == "json" %}
```json
{
  "output_format": "text",
  "color": true,
  "verbose": false
}
```
{% endif %}

### Environment Variables

All config keys can be overridden via environment variables prefixed with `{{ project_name | upper | replace("-", "_") }}_`:

```bash
export {{ project_name | upper | replace("-", "_") }}_OUTPUT_FORMAT=json
export {{ project_name | upper | replace("-", "_") }}_VERBOSE=true
```

Priority order (highest to lowest): CLI flags > environment variables > config file > defaults.
{% endif %}

